ow safe she felt, though she always knew the tremendous skill that was found within those of this guild.  <br><br>She resolved herself to do her best to learn of them, even as she was commanded to serve them to the best of her ability.<br>Perhaps she would somehow have allies, in her fight to remove this conditioning placed upon her by the dark elves, and to save the love of her life.<br><br>Fenwyn <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub37.ezboard.com/unanookt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nanook T</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ph3aR my witty sig</span><br>  Posts: 320<br> <font color=#70DB93>(3/8/02 10:44:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub37.ezboard.com/flexinvictusfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=70.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Plight of Prejudice</span><hr size=1> A snuffling, snorting sound at the hem of her dress brought her attention quickly around to face a medium-sized brown bear.  It paused in it's inspection of her to glance up and meet her gaze, it's head cocked slightly to the side in curiosity.<br><br>&quot;'Ere now, Pooh!  Don' bodder da priddy laydee!  Ahm sorry Miss Fenwyn, Miss.  'Ol Pooh 'ere hasn seen many light skin-types.  'E jus wanned ta see if ya smelled differnt.&quot;<br><br>The voice belonged to a massive hulk of an Ogre, just now sitting up in the corner chair he always occupied.  He whistled, a high pitched, keening sound, and the bear spun around and lumbered back to where this odd Ogre sat.  After a moment of low bass rumbling and muttering from the Ogre to the bear (and low bass rumbling and grunting from bear to Ogre), he looked up once more and grimaced at her in what could only be a valiant attempt at a reassuring smile.<br><br>&quot;Pardon me Miss Fenwyn, Miss.  We ain't even been intro-ducted proper-like.&quot;, he said.  &quot;I'm Nannuuk&quot;, he told her with a respectful nod, &quot; 'an dis 'ere is my Pooh-bear.  Say 'ello Pooh.&quot;, to which the bear likewise nodded in it's own bearlike fashion.  &quot;We knows yer kinda new 'ere, so if'n we can help ya out wif anythin', jus say da word.  If'n ya can't find me, jus tell Pooh.  Pooh can find me anywhere, can't ya Pooh?&quot;  <br><br>&quot;Whuf.&quot;, said the bear. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub37.ezboard.com/blexinvictus.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=gruuzgrimeyfingurz>GruuzGrimeyfingurz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>RaZoRwaLl or something like that.</span><br>  Posts: 80<br> <font color=#70DB93>(3/11/02 12:14:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub37.ezboard.com/flexinvictusfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=70.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Plight of Prejudice</span><hr size=1> Yet another ogre stuck his head into the room.  &quot;Nan,&quot; he grumbled, &quot;wye joo gotta be messin wit da gestz?  Joo noez beddur dan ta let dat dar bar in heer.  Himz myte maak da mess on da leddy Synn'z carpetz, an sheez nott gunna lyke dat.&quot;<br><br>He nodded at the other figure in the room.  &quot;H'lo dar,&quot; he said,  &quot;Meez Gruuz iz.  Welkum too da fambly.&quot;  With that, he withdrew, motioning for Nannuuk to do the same. <p>Gruuz Grimeyfingurz, Craknek uv da Lex Invictus fambly... pikklez er guud wit cheez.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub37.ezboard.com/unanookt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nanook T</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ph3aR my witty sig</span><br>  Posts: 340<br> <font color=#70DB93>(3/12/02 5:22:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub37.ezboard.com/flexinvictusfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=70.topic&index=6>Reply</a> 